{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860054686,"sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","part":{"id":"prt_d7981f77d0019X37h4BuqESrjB","messageID":"msg_d7981d6b6001G8P0HdhCnQcUPd","sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0d7fa081a25e4ae3959f4c8c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md","offset":1143},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1143:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n1144:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n1145:         self.stderr = stderr\n1146:         self.command = command\n1147:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n1148: \n1149: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n1150:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n1151:     pass\n1152: \n1153: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n1154:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n1155:     pass\n1156: ```\n1157: \n1158: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n1159: \n1160: ```toml\n1161: dependencies = [\n1162:     \"requests\",\n1163:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n1164:     \"cryptography\",\n1165: ]\n1166: ```\n1167: \n1168: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n1169: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n1170: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n1171: \n1172: \n1173: --- python-sdk/spec.md ---\n1174: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n1175: \n1176: ## Purpose\n1177: \n1178: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n1179: \n1180: ## Requirements\n1181: \n1182: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n1183: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n1184: \n1185: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n1186: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n1187: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n1188: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n1189: \n1190: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n1191: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n1192: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n1193: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n1194: \n1195: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n1196: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n1197: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n1198: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n1199: \n1200: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n1201: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n1202: \n1203: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n1204: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n1205: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n1206: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n1207: \n1208: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n1209: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n1210: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n1211: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n1212: \n1213: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n1214: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n1215: \n1216: #### Scenario: Context manager\n1217: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n1218: - **WHEN** the block exits\n1219: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n1220: \n1221: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n1222: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n1223: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n1224: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n1225: \n1226: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n1227: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n1228: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n1229: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n1230: \n1231: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n1232: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n1233: \n1234: #### Scenario: Create session\n1235: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n1236: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n1237: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n1238: \n1239: #### Scenario: Delete session\n1240: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n1241: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n1242: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n1243: \n1244: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n1245: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n1246: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n1247: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n1248: \n1249: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n1250: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n1251: \n1252: #### Scenario: Execute command\n1253: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n1254: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n1255: \n1256: #### Scenario: Files API\n1257: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n1258: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n1259: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n1260: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n1261: \n1262: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n1263: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n1264: \n1265: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n1266: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n1267: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n1268: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n1269: \n1270: ### Requirement: Session header management\n1271: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n1272: \n1273: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n1274: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n1275: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n1276: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n1277: \n1278: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n1279: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n1280: \n1281: #### Scenario: Command failure\n1282: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n1283: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n1284: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n1285: \n1286: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n1287: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n1288: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n1289: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n1290: \n1291: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n1292: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n1293: \n1294: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n1295: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n1296: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n1297: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n1298: \n1299: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n1300: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n1301: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n1302: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n1303: \n1304: ---\n1305: \n1306: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n1307: \n1308: \n1309: Use OpenSpec format. Each requirement must have acceptance scenarios.\n\n(End of file - total 1309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775860054675,"end":1775860054684}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775860054712,"sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","part":{"id":"prt_d7981fa9e001fZlpYWXbJ0KkKI","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7981d6b6001G8P0HdhCnQcUPd","sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":31239,"input":16091,"output":254,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14894}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775860059341,"sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","part":{"id":"prt_d79820ccb001nYqaS0KGREd5Um","messageID":"msg_d7981facc001F4ZlnHnAoEttq3","sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860097943,"sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","part":{"id":"prt_d798216e50016nWQ5y458tk6O0","messageID":"msg_d7981facc001F4ZlnHnAoEttq3","sessionID":"ses_2867e396cffeXyILg3kxWXjsTN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_69eca6a55fe2419988efce9e","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec — AR-020: CLI pack command\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines the acceptance scenarios for the `pack` command in the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`), which validates and prepares a workspace for building and publishing AI agents.\n\n**AR ID:** AR-020  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Workspace validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and contains valid agent source files based on the specified language before proceeding with packaging.\n\n### Scenario: Valid Python workspace\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with a Python agent (default language)\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that at least one `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n### Scenario: Valid Java workspace\n- **GIVEN** a workspace directory exists at the specified path\n- **WHEN** `pack` is executed with `--language java`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL validate that `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n- **AND** the workspace SHALL be considered valid for packaging\n\n### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist or is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the directory does not exist\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` resolves to `\"python\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` file exists in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Java workspace without pom.xml\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `pom.xml` does not exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")`\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Metadata loading and merging\n\nThe system SHALL load existing agent metadata from the workspace and merge CLI option overrides to create a complete metadata configuration.\n\n### Scenario: Load existing metadata\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the metadata using `MetadataService.load_metadata`\n- **AND** return an `AgentMetadata` object with all fields populated\n\n### Scenario: Fallback metadata file loading\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does NOT exist in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL attempt to load `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` as fallbacks\n- **AND** raise `FileNotFoundError` if none of the fallback files exist\n\n### Scenario: Create new metadata with defaults\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values:\n  - `language`: `\"python\"`\n  - `port`: `8080`\n  - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n  - `requirements_file`: `\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n### Scenario: CLI option overrides\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options are provided\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL override metadata fields with CLI-provided values:\n  - `--agent-name` overrides `agent_name`\n  - `--language` overrides `language`\n  - `--entrypoint` overrides `entrypoint`\n  - `--port` overrides `port`\n  - `--build-mode` overrides `build_mode`\n  - `--description` overrides `description`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Dockerfile generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a Dockerfile in the workspace when packaging Python or Java agents, based on the language and entrypoint configuration.\n\n### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_python_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include:\n  - Base Python image\n  - Working directory setup\n  - Dependency installation from `requirements.txt` (if exists)\n  - Entrypoint command from metadata\n  - Port exposure\n\n### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a Dockerfile using `_generate_java_dockerfile`\n- **AND** the Dockerfile SHALL include:\n  - Base Maven/Java image\n  - Dependency installation via `mvn`\n  - Entrypoint command from metadata\n  - Port exposure\n\n### Scenario: Skip Dockerfile when already exists\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `_generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n- **AND** return `None` indicating no new Dockerfile was generated\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Dependency processing\n\nThe system SHALL process agent dependencies based on the language, ensuring all required packages are available for the Docker build.\n\n### Scenario: Process Python dependencies\n- **GIVEN** `requirements.txt` exists in a Python workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the requirements file format\n- **AND** include it in the package output\n\n### Scenario: Process Java dependencies\n- **GIVEN** `pom.xml` exists in a Java workspace\n- **WHEN** `_process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate the POM file exists\n- **AND** include it in the package output\n\n### Scenario: Missing Python requirements file\n- **GIVEN** workspace language is Python but `requirements.txt` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning but continue (requirements are optional)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Output preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for the packaged workspace and update metadata with final resolved values.\n\n### Scenario: Default output path\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the original workspace path as the output\n\n### Scenario: Custom output path\n- **GIVEN** `--output` specifies a custom directory path\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the output directory if it does not exist\n- **AND** copy the workspace contents to the output path\n\n### Scenario: Update metadata after packaging\n- **GIVEN** packaging completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save the final `AgentMetadata` to `{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **AND** include the dockerfile path if one was generated\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — CLI interface\n\nThe system SHALL expose the `pack` command via Typer with specific options and display formatted output to the user.\n\n### Scenario: Pack command options\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display options:\n  - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n  - `--agent-name NAME` — Override agent name\n  - `--language LANG` — Programming language (python, java)\n  - `--entrypoint CMD` — Override entrypoint command\n  - `--port PORT` — Port to expose (default: 8080)\n  - `--build-mode MODE` — Build strategy (local, cloud)\n  - `--description TEXT` — Agent description\n  - `--output PATH` — Output path for packaged workspace\n  - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n\n### Scenario: Successful pack output\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with all required files\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message using Rich `Progress` spinner\n- **AND** display:\n  - Agent name\n  - Resolved workspace path\n  - Metadata file path (`{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml`)\n\n### Scenario: Pack failure with verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red: `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}`\n- **AND** print full traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Pack failure without verbose\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Language compatibility validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the specified language is compatible with the workspace contents.\n\n### Scenario: Valid language specification\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as `\"python\"` or `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `_validate_language_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL pass successfully\n\n### Scenario: Invalid language specification\n- **GIVEN** `--language` is provided as an unsupported value\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating valid options are `python` or `java`\n\n### Scenario: Port range validation\n- **GIVEN** `--port` is provided with a value outside valid range\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validator runs on the metadata\n- **THEN** validation SHALL fail with `ValueError` indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `pack` command — Entrypoint inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command if not explicitly provided, based on the workspace language and structure.\n\n### Scenario: Infer Python entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Python agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for `main.py` in the workspace root\n- **AND** default to `python main.py` if found\n\n### Scenario: Infer Java entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** `--entrypoint` is not provided for a Java agent\n- **WHEN** `_infer_entrypoint` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL look for a main class in `pom.xml`\n- **AND** default to `java -jar target/*.jar` if a JAR is expected\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n- CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775860097934,"end":1775860097940}}}}
